quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  49,1,"O you who have believed, do not put [yourselves] before Allāh and His Messenger<sup foot_note=197401>1</sup> but fear Allāh. Indeed, Allāh is Hearing and Knowing.",footnotes:197401:1
  49,2,"O you who have believed, do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet or be loud to him in speech like the loudness of some of you to others, lest your deeds become worthless while you perceive not."
  49,3,"Indeed, those who lower their voices before the Messenger of Allāh - they are the ones whose hearts Allāh has tested for righteousness. For them is forgiveness and great reward."
  49,4,"Indeed, those who call you, [O Muḥammad], from behind the chambers - most of them do not use reason."